page.title: 12EAST PEMBROKE DOCK- INDUSTRY
page.content: The north-east part of Pembroke Dock has been declared an 'Enterprise zone' to attract industry to the area Unemployment has been very high in the town for many years and many factories including 3 in the block,have closed. The zone uses land reclaimed from the mud of Cosheston Creek.For many years,the area was used as the Council rubbish tip.This was recently levelled off and covered with soil and it is hoped that new industries will come to give much- needed jobs to the area. Some small firms have already opened in the zone. The land bordering the Cleddau River in the west of the block is owned by the Admiralty and there were many large oil tanks there until recently. H.M.S. Warrior,the first iron-hulled warship (built in 1860) was used as an oiling jetty until not long ago.
